# UPLIFTLY - Requirements Document

## Project Overview

UPLIFTLY is an AI-powered platform designed to help video content creators analyze and optimize their content before publishing. By leveraging advanced AI capabilities, the platform provides actionable insights, engagement recommendations, and improvement suggestions to maximize content performance.

## Vision

To empower content creators with intelligent, data-driven insights that transform raw video content into optimized, high-performing media that resonates with their target audience.

## MVP Features

### 1. User Authentication
- Secure user registration and login
- Password recovery and account management
- Session management and token-based authentication
- Role-based access control

### 2. Dashboard
- Personalized user dashboard
- Overview of uploaded videos and analysis history
- Quick access to recent recommendations
- Performance metrics summary

### 3. Video Upload
- Drag-and-drop video upload interface
- Support for multiple video formats
- Upload progress tracking
- File size validation and error handling
- Metadata capture (title, description, tags)

### 4. AI Content Analysis
- Automated video content analysis using AI
- Content quality assessment
- Topic and theme identification
- Sentiment analysis
- Pacing and engagement pattern detection

### 5. Recommendation Engine
- AI-generated improvement suggestions
- Engagement optimization recommendations
- Content structure analysis
- Best practices guidance
- Actionable insights for content enhancement

## Technology Stack

### Frontend
- **Framework**: Next.js with React
- **Hosting**: Amazon S3 (static hosting)
- **CDN**: Amazon CloudFront for global content delivery
- **UI/UX**: Responsive design for desktop and mobile

### Backend
- **Runtime**: Node.js with Express.js
- **Compute**: AWS Lambda (serverless architecture)
- **API Gateway**: Amazon API Gateway for RESTful APIs
- **Architecture**: Microservices-based serverless design

### Database
- **Primary Database**: Amazon DynamoDB
- **Data Model**: NoSQL schema for user data, video metadata, and analysis results

### Storage
- **Media Storage**: Amazon S3
- **Storage Classes**: Intelligent tiering for cost optimization
- **Access Control**: IAM policies and bucket policies

### AI Layer
- **AI Service**: Amazon Bedrock
- **Capabilities**: Content analysis, natural language processing, recommendation generation
- **Models**: Foundation models for video content understanding

### Authentication
- **Service**: Amazon Cognito
- **Features**: User pools, identity federation, MFA support

### Monitoring & Logging
- **Service**: Amazon CloudWatch
- **Metrics**: Application performance, API usage, error tracking
- **Logs**: Centralized logging for debugging and auditing

## Deployment Requirements

### Infrastructure
- AWS account with appropriate service limits
- IAM roles and policies configured
- VPC and security groups (if applicable)
- Domain name and SSL certificate (optional for MVP)

### Environment Configuration
- Development, staging, and production environments
- Environment variables for API keys and secrets
- AWS credentials and region configuration

### CI/CD Pipeline
- Automated build and deployment process
- Infrastructure as Code (IaC) using AWS CloudFormation or Terraform
- Version control with Git

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18 or higher)
- AWS CLI configured
- npm or yarn package manager

## Success Metrics

### User Engagement
- Number of registered users
- Daily/monthly active users
- Average session duration
- User retention rate

### Platform Performance
- Video upload success rate
- Average analysis completion time
- API response time (< 500ms for 95th percentile)
- System uptime (99.9% target)

### AI Accuracy
- Recommendation relevance score
- User satisfaction with AI insights
- Accuracy of content analysis

### Business Metrics
- Number of videos analyzed
- User feedback and ratings
- Feature adoption rate
- Cost per analysis

### Technical Metrics
- Lambda cold start time
- S3 upload/download speed
- DynamoDB read/write latency
- CloudFront cache hit ratio

## Future Roadmap

### Phase 2 Features
- Thumbnail optimization with A/B testing suggestions
- Engagement prediction based on historical data
- SEO improvement suggestions for video metadata
- Advanced analytics dashboard with trend analysis

### Phase 3 Features
- Multi-platform content optimization
- Collaborative features for teams
- Integration with popular video platforms
- Real-time content performance tracking
